	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />At 1.79 MHz, any wave with fewer than about 81 clocks per cycle will be inaudible (above 22 kHz). If my calculation is right, a raw period of 4 or less will be above 22 kHz (4 results in timer period of 4*2+2=10, and wave period of 10*8=80).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


