		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The NES audio output includes some kind of low-pass filter (probably for the sake of the RF unit), so it seems <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heterodyne" class="postlink">heterodyning</a> wouldn't occur anyway.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
